    "title_html": "What you're <em>looking</em> at.",
    "prose_paragraphs": [
      "The most common asphalt-shingle install nationally is a gray in this exact tonal zone. COASTAL GRANITE sits right inside that fairway: dark enough to feel anchored, light enough to keep the elevation breathing. The granule blend is engineered to read as a single quiet plane from the street.",
      "Atlas uses a tight blend of dark gray and faint blue-gray granules to keep the surface visually alive. The result is a roof that reads as a clean architectural line from the street and a textured surface up close.",
      "Works well with crisp white trim, warm wood accents, and natural stone. Slightly cooler than the brown family, so it tends to pair better with blue, sage, and gray sidings than with yellow or peach."
    ],
